notes: Rory McIlroy earned his 19th PGA TOUR title and third at the Wells Fargo Championship, recording a final-round 68 to defeat Abraham Ancer by one stroke. The victory came in McIlroy's 196th career start at the age of 32 years, 5 days.

McIlroy became the 45th player all-time to reach 19 career wins on TOUR, with the win marking his first since the 2019 World Golf Championships-HSBC Champions. McIlroy entered the final round trailing by two strokes, collecting the 10th come-from-behind win of his career.
The Wells Fargo Championship became the first PGA TOUR event which McIlroy won three times.
Third-round leader Keith Mitchell finished T3 after holding the 54-hole lead/co-lead for the first time in his PGA TOUR career.
